":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec0yhfBT9y9TBC75","ref":"John.8.1","text":"Jesus went unto the mount of Olives.","year":33},{"id":"reckTIYBBsDdod9qI","ref":"John.8.2","text":"And early in the morning he came again into the temple, and all the people came unto him; and he sat down, and taught them.","year":33},{"id":"rec3KttPBJ5trZerf","ref":"John.8.3","text":"And the scribes and Pharisees brought unto him a woman taken in adultery; and when they had set her in the midst,","year":33},{"id":"reciqq7yHXvVC4AAk","ref":"John.8.4","text":"They say unto him, Master, this woman was taken in adultery, in the very act.","year":33},{"id":"rechlzf2qZHoiU3AT","ref":"John.8.5","text":"Now Moses in the law commanded us, that such should be stoned: but what sayest thou?","year":33},{"id":"rectbx1FqJ0WTSUw7","ref":"John.8.6","text":"This they said, tempting him, that they might have to accuse him. But Jesus stooped down, and with his finger wrote on the ground, as though he heard them not.","year":33},{"id":"recjnhRAgDgUxW8UX","ref":"John.8.7","text":"So when they continued asking him, he lifted up himself, and said unto them, He that is without sin among you, let him first cast a stone at her.","year":33},{"id":"recDL4JrjcPtiiqWD","ref":"John.8.8","text":"And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground.","year":33}]}
